Lesson 1: The Rich don’t work for money

Most people are governed by two emotions: Fear and Greed. Fear that they will not have enough to pay their bills, and Greed of all the other things they want to buy. The Fear of not having enough money motivates us to work hard, and then when we get that paycheck, greed or desires start us to think of all the wonderful things money can buy. The pattern is then set: Get up. Go to work. Pay bills. Offer them more money, and they will continue this cycle by increasing their spending. This is called the rat race. People get up and go to work, hoping that money will quell their Fear.

Other people work for desire. They spend money to fulfill that desire, but that desire could never be satisfied, it just grows, so they spend more and more and more.

Fear and Desire/Greed are emotions you should avoid in handling money. We can observe our emotions, but we should not let them govern us. 

Fear pushes you out the door, and desire calls to you. That’s the trap.

