Rule # 1: Know the difference between Assets and Liabilities, and buy Assets

Peope who get quick money often finds themselves again in the same financial mess or worse than before

Money accentuates the cash flow pattern in your head. If your pattern is to spend, then Increase in cash will just increase in spending.

Financial aptitude - what you do with your money

Wealth - how many days forward without cash inflow you can survive (Buckman Fuller) - Survivability. The moment you achieved an amount from your income-generating asset equal to your cash outflow, then you will be wealthy. If you want to increase your cash outflow, then you should increase your cash inflow by the same amount to maintain the same level of wealth. You become independent from your wages. You become more focused on acquiring income generating assets.

Goal: Excess money from your income generating asset -> reinvested to acquire more income-generating assets

The rich buy assets, the poor only has expenses, the middle class buy liabilities they think are assets!

The rich is focused on their assets, the others focused on their income statements

