How to start?

10 steps to develop your financial genius:
1. Find a reason greater than reality - the power of spirit

What don’t you want on your current reality now? What do you want to have when you achieve financial freedom? These reasons should be stronger than reality. 

2. Make daily choices - the power of choice
Invest in your gratest asset - your
Mind

3. Choose your friends carefully - The power of association

Rich people often talk about money, not to brag, but because their minds have adapted to it. Poor people go to them not to ask how they did it, but to get a loan or a job. 

Don’t listen to poor or frightened people. They are the chicken littles of life. They always tell you why something won’t work. 

4. Master a formula and then learn a new one - the power of learning quickly

5. Pay yourself first - the power of self-discipline

A. Dont get into large debt positions that you have to pay for. Build your assets first. Keep your expenses low. Then, buy that house or car

B. When you come up short, let the pressure build up. Don’t dip in to your savings. Use the pressure to inspire your financial genius to cone io ways to make mire money, then pay your bills. 

Savings are only used to create more money, not pay bills!

6. Pay your brokers well - the power of good advice. 

Good professionals are expensive. But the information they give is priceless. 

If all you’re thinking about is cutting down their commission, then do you think they will have your best interest in mind?

Most people pay tips on waiters whole heartedly but are resistant on paying professionals for their assets. 

Manage and reward the people who are smarter than you. Ex. Board of directors

7. Be an Indian given - the power of giving something for nothing

Invest in something with ROI in mind. Ex. Invest in stocks for a company with forecasted growth in a month. When the prices go up, withdraw the initial amount and let the gains grow more. The initial amount is invested for another asset. 

Invest in something which makes you get something else for free. 

8. Use assets to buy luxuries - the power of focus

9. Choose heroes - the power of myths

Heroes make things look easy. If they can do it, so can I. 

10. Teach and ye shall receive - the power of giving

Tithe!

If you want something, you must first learn how to give. If you’re running short of something, give what you want first and it will come back to you in buckets. 

I want money so I give money, and money comes to me. I want sales, so I help someone get sales, and I get sales. Giving always works like magic. 

God does need to receive, but humans need to give. 

Poor people are more greedy than rich people. 

Your world is only a mirror of you. 

